# Step 2:

Add the `kambiAPIService` as a dependency to the controller

__`appController.js`__
```js
return $app.controller('appController', ['$scope', '$controller', 'kambiAPIService',
   function ( $scope, $controller, kambiAPIService ) {
```

Add a $scoppe variable to store the events
__`appController.js`__
```javascript
$scope.liveEvents = [];
```

#### Create a method that will call the json api with the help of the `kambiAPIService`.

__`appController.js`__
```javascript
$scope.getLiveEvents = function(){
   // The api method returns a promise, so we'll use 'then' to handle the resolution
   kambiAPIService.getLiveEvents().then(function(response){
      $scope.liveEvents = response.data.liveEvents;
   });
};
```

Now we call the method.
The init method returns a promise that is resolved when the all the configurations in the api services are set, so we wait for this to resolve and call
our function after that using ``then()``.

__`appController.js`__
```javascript
$scope.init().then(function () {
   $scope.getLiveEvents();
});
```
